` as a pure function in isolation; AC6's `make test` green-pass may not cover the `workflow_ops.py` integration if existing tests don't exercise the Pass-4 coach step with advisory findings.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f79989502b403beca","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"## Scope — `workflow_ops.py` bullet; ## Acceptance Criteria (all ACs)","norm_id":"n6aa8ab0c2ddfd45c","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add AC: 'When `run_pass4_coach` (or equivalent `workflow_ops.py` entry point) is called with a mix of blocking and advisory decided findings, the returned result dict contains `result[\"coaching\"][\"triage\"]` as a non-empty list with every entry having keys `id`, `criteria`, `priority`, `block_threshold`, `bucket`, `reason`; blocking findings are absent. Proving command: `python -m pytest tests/test_plan_review_triage.py -k integration -q`.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.3333,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The plan describes a workflow integration deliverable — invoking `triage_advisories` in workflow_ops.py's Pass-4 coach step and attaching the resulting `triage` array to the returned verdict's coaching section — but no AC directly verifies that this integration wire-up is present and correct in the returned result. ACs 1–4 test the pure function in isolation; AC6 checks lint/typecheck/test green, but none asserts that the workflow actually returns a `triage` key in its coaching output.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fbc481589c4d525d9","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope (workflow_ops.py bullet) and What section (triage attached to plan-review RESULT) vs ACs 1–6","norm_id":"n6d0c8d4283f0d917","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.3333,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E6"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"AC5's proving command (`grep -q \"APPLY_NOW_MARGIN\" docs/plan-review-gate.md`) proves only that the string 'APPLY_NOW_MARGIN' appears somewhere in the file, but the AC requires documentation of four distinct elements: (1) the triage stage, (2) the ranking rule including the APPLY_NOW_MARGIN default, (3) the ordering and defer-reason format, and (4) the R7 dogfood expectation. A single grep hit satisfies the command but leaves elements 1, 3, and 4 entirely unverified.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f8f74ea22994d8cee","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"## Acceptance Criteria — AC5","norm_id":"n4ce5fa137f7b0990","priority":0.55,"reason":"veto:cited-reference-inaccurate","scenarios":[],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Replace the single grep with: `grep -qE 'APPLY_NOW_MARGIN.*0\\.10' docs/plan-review-gate.md && grep -q 'apply-now' docs/plan-review-gate.md && grep -q 'R7' docs/plan-review-gate.md && grep -qE 'deferred:.*block' docs/plan-review-gate.md` — each grep anchors one of the four stated documentation requirements.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"no","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Name the bespoke orchestrator file (e.g. `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/orchestrator.py` or wherever it lives) in the Scope section so both call-site locations are explicit and the symmetry AC can be independently verified.","cohort":["E3","G5","T6"],"criteria":["E3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["Plan names `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/workflow_ops.py` for the main path but provides no file path for the bespoke orchestrator.","ABSENCE: no file path, no pointer to the bespoke orchestrator module anywhere in the plan."],"finding":"The Scope section states 'the bespoke orchestrator path is updated symmetrically for parity' but never names the file that contains this bespoke path. `workflow_ops.py` is named for the main path, but the bespoke orchestrator file is unspecified, leaving the implementer unable to locate the second call-site from the plan alone.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f5ce9479f3ad6c89a","impact":0.536,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section — 'the bespoke orchestrator path is updated symmetrically for parity'","norm_id":"na7d07317285cd8a8","priority":0.335,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Implementer modifies only `workflow_ops.py`, missing the bespoke orchestrator path, so agents using that path never see `verdict['triage']` — a silent behavioral gap."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"In the Scope bullet for `workflow_ops.py`, add a companion bullet: `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/<orchestrator_file>.py — in the bespoke orchestrator path, invoke triage_advisories on surviving advisory findings and set verdict[\"triage\"] before the closing return (symmetric with the workflow_ops.py change).`","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify the error-handling posture for the `triage_advisories` call in `plan_review_coach_notes`: either (a) wrap in try/except with `verdict['triage'] = []` on failure (matching the existing `pass2_completion` DEGRADE pattern), or (b) document that any exception is intentionally allowed to propagate (failing the coach step).","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["Plan says: 'invoke `triage_advisories` on the surviving advisory findings and set `verdict[\"triage\"]` before the closing `validate_structured(verdict, _OUTPUT_SCHEMA)` return'","No try/except or fallback behavior is specified for `triage_advisories` in the plan","ABSENCE: the plan does not specify the error-handling posture for this new call site","Existing pattern: `pass2_completion` in `passes.py` wraps its sub-call in `try/except Exception` with a documented DEGRADE path (returns `{}`) — the plan does not indicate whether `triage_advisories` should follow the same pattern"],"finding":"No fallback is specified for `triage_advisories` raising an exception inside `plan_review_coach_notes` (the `plan_review_coach` step). If the pure function raises (e.g. a malformed finding missing `priority` or `block_threshold`), the whole coach step fails, triggering `_recover_plan_review_coach_failure`, which produces a verdict with no triage and logs a coach error. The plan does not say whether the call should be wrapped in a try/except (returning `[]` on failure) or allowed to propagate.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f0e5e9d8dbf09b2c0","impact":0.536,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section — `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/workflow_ops.py` `plan_review_coach_notes` step","norm_id":"ncc4d1ee622d1896b","priority":0.335,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A finding missing `block_threshold` (e.g. a DET advisory finding that bypassed Pass-3) causes `triage_advisories` to raise a KeyError or TypeError; the coach step fails; `_recover_plan_review_coach_failure` fires; triage is absent and a coach-error is logged"],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Enumerate `src/rebar/llm/workflow/gate_dispatch.py` (`_recover_plan_review_coach_failure`) as a file to touch, or explicitly acknowledge that triage is intentionally omitted from coach-failure recovery verdicts and document the gap.","cohort":["G1G2"],"criteria":["G1G2"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["_recover_plan_review_coach_failure at gate_dispatch.py:287–328 calls orchestrator.finalize_verdict directly and returns a validated verdict, never touching plan_review_coach","Plan Scope: 'the bespoke orchestrator path is updated symmetrically for parity' — gate_dispatch.py is not in the Scope file list","The plan asserts: 'the returned plan-review verdict carries the `triage` array as top-level `verdict[\"triage\"]`' — this is false for recovery-path verdicts"],"finding":"The coach-failure recovery path `_recover_plan_review_coach_failure` in `gate_dispatch.py` assembles and returns a `plan_review_verdict` by calling `orchestrator.finalize_verdict` directly — bypassing the `plan_review_coach` step entirely. This means the triage array will be absent from verdicts emitted on that recovery path. The plan does not enumerate `gate_dispatch.py` as a file to touch and does not acknowledge this gap.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f85ed4c8def0127a7","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section ('the bespoke orchestrator path is updated symmetrically for parity') and `src/rebar/llm/workflow/gate_dispatch.py:287`","norm_id":"n235629aa7d08d77e","priority":0.2888,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A coach-step failure (e.g. LLM timeout mid-coach) triggers the recovery path; the returned verdict lacks `verdict['triage']`, silently breaking any downstream consumer expecting it.","R7's dogfood metric joins on triage data and finds it missing for coach-failure runs, introducing a data gap in the advisory-application-latency measurement."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify how `verdict['triage']` is populated (or explicitly omitted with a documented rationale) in the `_recover_plan_review_coach_failure` path in `gate_dispatch.py` — add `gate_dispatch.py` to the Scope section or add a note that triage is intentionally absent on coach-failure recovery verdicts.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["Plan says: 'the bespoke orchestrator path is updated symmetrically for parity'","`_recover_plan_review_coach_failure` calls `orchestrator.finalize_verdict(..., coaching=[])` then `_findings.validate_structured(verdict, 'plan_review_verdict')` — no `plan_review_coach` step involved, so `verdict['triage']` is never set on this path","ABSENCE: `gate_dispatch.py` is not listed in the plan's Scope section; the recovery function is an unspecified site"],"finding":"The coach-failure recovery path (`gate_dispatch._recover_plan_review_coach_failure`) assembles and returns a `plan_review_verdict` dict by calling `orchestrator.finalize_verdict` directly and then `_findings.validate_structured` — it bypasses `workflow_ops.plan_review_coach` entirely. This path will produce a verdict with no `triage` key. The plan says 'the bespoke orchestrator path is updated symmetrically for parity' but never names this recovery function, leaving it unaddressed.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f5cb5b13e52c9b66d","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section / `src/rebar/llm/workflow/gate_dispatch.py` `_recover_plan_review_coach_failure` (lines 287-328)","norm_id":"na13f6e02db594b1d","priority":0.2888,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Pass-4 coach step times out or raises mid-run; `_recover_plan_review_coach_failure` fires; returned verdict silently omits `triage`; agent cannot use triage for advisory coaching, defeating the feature's purpose on a coach-failure recovery"],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add `gate_dispatch.py` to the Scope section with a note: on the coach-failure recovery path (`_recover_plan_review_coach_failure`), set `verdict['triage'] = triage_advisories(parts['surfaced'])` before the `validate_structured` call, OR document explicitly that triage is omitted on recovery verdicts (since no LLM coaching ran, triage is moot).","tier":"LLM","validity":0.875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Anchor the `bucket` enum vocabulary ('apply-now' | 'defer') in a named constant or small Pydantic model in `passes.py` (e.g. `BUCKET_APPLY_NOW = 'apply-now'`; `BUCKET_DEFER = 'defer'`) so the AC determinism test and the bucketing logic share the same literal, preventing silent misspelling drift.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["Plan defines: `{\"id\": str, \"criteria\": list[str], \"priority\": float, \"block_threshold\": float, \"bucket\": \"apply-now\"|\"defer\", \"reason\": str}`","`plan_review_verdict.schema.json` confirmed: `\"additionalProperties\": true` at top level — triage items are unvalidated nested objects","No `triage` array or triage-item schema exists in `plan_review_verdict.schema.json`","ABSENCE: no Pydantic model or JSON Schema for triage item shape is specified in the plan"],"finding":"The `bucket` field in each triage entry is defined as an enum with exactly two values (`'apply-now'` | `'defer'`), but this vocabulary is never anchored in a schema or registered contract — it exists only in prose. Since `plan_review_verdict.schema.json` has `additionalProperties: true` and triage array items are nested objects, the enum is never validated at runtime. An implementer who misnames a bucket value (e.g. `'apply_now'` with an underscore) will produce silently wrong output.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fa7cef50600f2796f","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section / Output shape definition: `{\"bucket\": \"apply-now\"|\"defer\"}`","norm_id":"n3b2393c11904ccfa","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Implementer uses `'apply_now'` (underscore) instead of `'apply-now'` (hyphen); no validation catches it; downstream consumers (R7 dogfood metrics) silently see an unknown bucket value"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add `BUCKET_APPLY_NOW = 'apply-now'` and `BUCKET_DEFER = 'defer'` as module constants in `passes.py` alongside `APPLY_NOW_MARGIN`, and have `triage_advisories` use them — this co-locates the enum vocabulary with the function that emits it.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}}],"impact_model_version":"plan-v3","material_fingerprint":"e4d283b9d614c214","metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":229.4,"llm_calls":29,"llm_ms":627313.6,"total_ms":627685.1,"verify_requests":35},"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","regver":"b293b9a55de591cc","runner":"pydantic_ai","schema":"plan_review_result_v2","ticket_id":"5dac-c177-56ff-4af4","ticket_type":"story","verdict":"BLOCK","verified_at_sha":"43d1545237745f4666dcc13c81587c824251e51d"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"REVIEW_RESULT","timestamp":1784253846922608001,"uuid":"266857cf-a2cd-45a1-8536-f6a60eac3b66"}